Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a new version of the Calculus of Inductive Constructions (CIC) which is a logical framework used in proof assistants like Coq. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the outsourcing of computation to first-order decision procedures, which can be seen as a programming language feature. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach for building in first-order decision procedures in a safe and incremental way, which can be relevant to software engineering practices. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of decision procedures, which can be seen as a type of machine learning algorithm. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the soundness of the system and the certificate checkers, which can be related to computational complexity analysis.
